.. erbsland-ansi::
    :escape-char: ‚êõ
    :theme: ela-term

    ‚êõ[92mcommand-line-help‚êõ[37m [‚êõ[35m<options>‚êõ[37m]

    ‚êõ[97mSummary
    ‚êõ[37mThis demo prints a fictive command-line help page that adapts to the terminal
    width. On wider terminals it uses ‚êõ[97mTerminal::printParagraph()‚êõ[37m to keep
    descriptions aligned, wrapped, and easy to scan. Below 40 columns it
    intentionally falls back to plain line-oriented output so you can compare both
    styles.

    ‚êõ[97mPreview Paragraph
    ‚êõ[93;44mPreview ‚êõ[97mThis paragraph keeps a visible background so options like background
    mode, wrap markers, word breaks, ellipsis handling, and alignment become easier
    to inspect while you adjust the rendering settings.

    ‚êõ[49mOptions
    ‚êõ[96m--help‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-h‚êõ[97m                          ‚êõ[37mRender this formatted help output. The flag
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mis mostly here so the demo behaves like a
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mfamiliar command-line tool.
    ‚êõ[96m--terminal-width‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-t‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<columns>‚êõ[97m      ‚êõ[37mDisable automatic width detection and
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37msimulate a terminal width between 20 and 200
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mcells for deterministic wrapping.
    ‚êõ[96m--description-column‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-c‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<column>‚êõ[97m   ‚êõ[37mOverride the description tab stop for the
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37moptions list with a fixed value. Valid values
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mare 12 to 60.
    ‚êõ[96m--maximum-description-column‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-d‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<column>
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mCap the automatically chosen description tab
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mstop. The default is 35 to force some
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mwrapping in the options list. Valid values
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mare 20 to 60.
    ‚êõ[96m--alignment‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-a‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<left|center|right>‚êõ[97m ‚êõ[37mChoose the horizontal alignment used for the
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mwrapped preview paragraphs.
    ‚êõ[96m--line-indent‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-l‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<columns>‚êõ[97m         ‚êõ[37mIndent the preview paragraphs by 0 to 10
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mcolumns before any wrapping takes place.
    ‚êõ[96m--first-line-indent‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-f‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<columns>‚êõ[97m   ‚êõ[37mOverride the first-line indent for preview
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mparagraphs. Valid values are 0 to 12.
    ‚êõ[96m--wrapped-line-indent‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-w‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<columns>‚êõ[97m ‚êõ[37mOverride the indentation of wrapped lines.
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mValues between 0 and 30 make the effect easy
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mto inspect.
    ‚êõ[96m--background-mode‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-b‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<mode>‚êõ[97m        ‚êõ[37mSet the background fill strategy: default,
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mwrapped-left, wrapped-right, wrapped-both,
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mfull-right, or full-both.
    ‚êõ[96m--line-break-start-mark‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-s‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<text>‚êõ[97m  ‚êõ[37mInsert a one- or two-character marker at the
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mstart of each wrapped continuation line.
    ‚êõ[96m--line-break-end-mark‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-m‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<text>‚êõ[97m    ‚êõ[37mAppend a one- or two-character marker at the
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mright edge when a line wraps.
    ‚êõ[96m--paragraph-spacing‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-p‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<single|double>
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mSwitch between compact paragraphs or
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mdouble-spaced output with one empty row in
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mbetween.
    ‚êõ[96m--word-separators‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-i‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<tokens>‚êõ[97m      ‚êõ[37mUse comma-separated separator tokens such as
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mspace,tab,slash or one-character literals
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mlike ; and |.
    ‚êõ[96m--word-break-mark‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-k‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<char>‚êõ[97m        ‚êõ[37mSet the single character inserted when a word
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mis split because it does not fit on the
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mcurrent line.
    ‚êõ[96m--maximum-line-wraps‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-r‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<count>‚êõ[97m    ‚êõ[37mLimit the number of automatic wraps per
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mparagraph. Use 0 for unlimited or values up
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mto 8 to trigger ellipsis behaviour.
    ‚êõ[96m--paragraph-ellipsis-mark‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-x‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<text>
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mChoose the marker that signals clipped
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mparagraphs after the configured wrap limit
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mhas been reached.
    ‚êõ[96m--tab-stops‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-u‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<list>‚êõ[97m              ‚êõ[37mProvide comma-separated tab stops like
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37m1,24,40 or use wrapped to align a stop with
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mthe wrapped-line indent.
    ‚êõ[96m--on-error‚êõ[37m/‚êõ[93m-o‚êõ[37m=‚êõ[35m<plain|empty>‚êõ[97m        ‚êõ[37mChoose the fallback when the paragraph cannot
    ‚êõ[97m                                   ‚êõ[37mbe laid out: plain output or empty output.

    ‚êõ[97mTry It
    ‚êõ[37mExperiment with ‚êõ[96m--terminal-width‚êõ[37m, wrap markers, custom tab stops, and the
    preview paragraph settings to see how a real command help screen can stay
    readable across narrow and wide terminals.‚êõ[0m
